## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- **Python 3.8+**
- **Twilio Account** (free trial available at https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio)

### Step 1: Clone and Install

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/kbornfas/Phone-locator.git
cd Phone-locator

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# Activate virtual environment
# On Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate
# On Linux/Mac:
source venv/bin/activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install as CLI tool
pip install -e .
```

### Step 2: Configure Twilio Credentials

1. Sign up at https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio
2. Get your credentials from the Twilio Console:
   - **Account SID** (starts with `AC...`)
   - **Auth Token**
   - **Phone Number** (buy or use trial number)

3. Configure the CLI:

```bash
phonetracker config --set voip.account_sid=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
phonetracker config --set voip.auth_token=your_auth_token_here
phonetracker config --set voip.phone_number=+1234567890
```

### Step 3: Verify Configuration

```bash
phonetracker config --show
phonetracker info
```

## ğŸ“– Usage

### Track a Phone Number

```bash
# Basic tracking (makes a call)
phonetracker track +254712345678

# Track with specific method
phonetracker track +254712345678 --method basic

# Silent mode (no confirmation prompts)
phonetracker track +254712345678 --silent

# Location lookup only (no call)
phonetracker track +254712345678 --no-call

# Custom timeout
phonetracker track +254712345678 --timeout 30
```

### Expected Output

```
âš ï¸  LEGAL AUTHORIZATION REQUIRED
This will make a call to the target number.
