## ğŸ› ï¸ Troubleshooting

### "Twilio credentials not configured"
```bash
phonetracker config --set voip.account_sid=ACxxx
phonetracker config --set voip.auth_token=xxx
phonetracker config --set voip.phone_number=+1xxx
```

### "Call not answered"
- Verify the phone number is correct (E.164 format: +1234567890)
- Ensure Twilio account has sufficient balance
- Trial accounts can only call verified numbers

### "ModuleNotFoundError"
```bash
pip install -e .
# or
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Low location accuracy
- The `basic` method only provides city-level accuracy
- For better accuracy, you need carrier API access (commercial)

## ğŸ”’ Security & Compliance

### Data Storage
- All tracking data is stored locally in SQLite
- Config file: `~/.phonetracker/config.yaml`
- Database: `~/.phonetracker/history.db`

### Audit Logging
- All tracking attempts are logged
- Includes timestamp, user, and result
- View with: `phonetracker logs`

### Legal Compliance Checklist
- [ ] User consent obtained
- [ ] Terms of service created
- [ ] Privacy policy in place
- [ ] Audit logging enabled
- [ ] Data retention policy defined
- [ ] GDPR/CCPA compliance verified

